Smart Parking System | Arduino Embedded Systems Project
Developed an automated smart parking system using Arduino to monitor parking slot occupancy, control vehicle access, and track parking duration. The system integrates multiple infrared sensors to detect vehicles in three parking spaces and dynamically update slot availability using LED indicators and serial monitoring.
A servo-controlled gate mechanism manages vehicle entry and exit, allowing access only when parking spaces are available. The system also records vehicle parking duration using Arduino timing functions and calculates a basic parking fee based on time spent in each slot.
The project demonstrates practical implementation of embedded system design, sensor integration, real-time monitoring, and automation logic in a small-scale smart infrastructure application.
Key Features
	•	Real-time parking slot detection using IR sensors
	•	Automated gate control using a servo motor
	•	LED-based visual indicators for slot availability
	•	Parking duration tracking and fee calculation
	•	Serial monitor interface for system status and diagnostics
Technologies: Arduino, Embedded C/C++, IR Sensors, Servo Motor, Sensor Integration
